---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Chess Engine | Sam Popham" noParticles>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Chess Engine — Deep Dive</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      A high-performance chess engine written in Python emphasising search
      efficiency and reproducibility.
    </p>

    <ul class="divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700">
      <!-- 1: Search tree visualization (image left) -->
      <li class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 py-12">
        <figure class="md:w-1/2 w-full">
          <!--
            Image guidance:
            High-quality screenshot of the engine's search tree visualization:
            - top-down tree layout showing nodes explored, PV highlighted,
            - dark background with coloured node highlights and thin connecting lines,
            - include HUD with nodes/sec and current depth.
          -->
          <img
            src="/src/assets/images/deep-dives/chess/initial-state.png"
            alt="Search tree visualization"
            class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg"
          />
        </figure>

        <article class="md:w-1/2 w-full">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Search Tree Visualization</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            Explore nodes and principal variations — see where pruning trims the
            branches and how the engine focuses its search.
          </p>
        </article>
      </li>

      <!-- 2: Sample board & best move (image right) -->
      <li
        class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:flex-row-reverse items-center gap-8 py-12"
      >
        <figure class="md:w-1/2 w-full">
          <!--
            Image guidance:
            Sample board position with suggested best move:
            - clean board screenshot with highlighted from→to move,
            - evaluation score and short rationale visible nearby.
          -->
          <img
            src="/src/assets/images/deep-dives/chess/mid-game.png"
            alt="Sample board with best move"
            class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg"
          />
        </figure>

        <article class="md:w-1/2 w-full">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">
            Sample Position & Best Move
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            A concrete example showing the engine's chosen move and a short
            explanation — checkmate your doubts with evidence.
          </p>
        </article>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Text-only sections for additional concepts -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8 mt-12">
      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Move-Order Heatmap</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Visualise how move ordering affects efficiency — because ordering
          matters when you want to be first in 'line'. A horizontal move list
          with colour-coded scores and timings highlights best moves and shows
          the ordering impact on node counts.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Performance Benchmarks</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Compare nodes/sec across depths — faster searches let you go deeper,
          so benchmark early and often. Clean line/area charts compare tuning
          runs with labelled axes, legend, and annotations.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
